Program: Discovery
Title: Robots - part two
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry27
Last Broadcast Date: 16 April 2002
An investigation into the robots of tomorrow, designed to work with people. The programme features Infanoid, a robot that has the mental ability of a one-year-old, and is learning to talk. Producers: Roland Pease/Andrew Luck-Baker. Picture: Robot with speech bubble, Credit: Thinkstock